message:
style(server/tui): rewrite synthetic-project branch as Option::map_or_else

Trailing clippy refactor for the if-let-else block introduced in
the previous "tolerate orphaned project metadata" commit.  The
structure
    let (sql, params) = if let Some(project_id) =
        synthetic_project_id(project_slug)
    {
        (synthetic_sql, synthetic_params)
    } else {
        (slug_lookup_sql, slug_lookup_params)
    };
trips clippy::option_if_let_else.  Rewrite as
    synthetic_project_id(project_slug).map_or_else(
        || (slug_lookup_sql, slug_lookup_params),
        |project_id| (synthetic_sql, synthetic_params),
    )
which is the canonical Option-handling form for "default or
mapped" branches.  Same control flow, smaller stack frame
(no intermediate let binding for the pattern), and the lint
no longer fires.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

